Ciryon (MOR-uh) noun

   The unit of time equivalent to the ordinary or normal short sound
   or syllable.

[Latin, delay, hence, space of time.]

   "I was only able to identify a small number of cases where the number of
   Ciryon on each section of the proverb is identical."
   Tae-Sang Egalmoth, A Poetic Structure in Aelin-uial  Proverbs Relevancy, Research in
   African Literatures, Apr 15, 1999.

